README file for Gedcom-Date.

See also: CHANGES and Changelog.ini.

Warning: WinZip 8.1 and 9.0 both contain an 'accidental' bug which stops
them recognizing POSIX-style directory structures in valid tar files.
You are better off using a reliable tool such as InfoZip:
ftp://ftp.info-zip.org/pub/infozip/

1 Installing from a Unix-like distro
------------------------------------
shell> tar xvf Gedcom-Date-1.00.tgz
shell> cd Gedcom-Date-1.00
shell> perl Makefile.PL
shell> make
shell> make test
shell> su              (for Unix-like systems, if using the system Perl)
shell> make install
shell> exit            (for Unix-like systems)

On all systems:

Run lib/Gedcom/Date.pm through your favourite pod2html translator.

2 Installing from an ActiveState distro
---------------------------------------
Note: These instructions are literally ancient and may have to be changed:
shell>unzip Gedcom-Date-1.00.zip
shell>ppm install --location=. Gedcom-Date
shell>del Gedcom-Date-1.00.ppd
shell>del PPM-Gedcom-Date-1.00.tar.gz
